&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;About BEES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Join us to build the future of B2B commerce!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;BEES is AB InBev’s B2B platform. Through our ecosystem,&amp;nbsp;merchants&amp;nbsp;and retailers across 29 countries can stock their businesses quickly, easily, and securely.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;At BEES, we dream big, lead with purpose, and develop technology that transforms the way retailers and sellers grow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Every line of code and every partnership is built in service of a single mission: to make commerce better for retailers and sellers around the world. Here, your work is not just important. It makes a difference!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;About this opportunity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the Senior Product Management role, you will join the BEES Fintech Core team, responsible for building the foundational services that power payment capabilities across multiple products. The team owns the platform that provides microservices and APIs used by different value streams, enabling seamless integration between frontend applications and back-office systems.&lt;br&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll work closely with Engineering, Solution Architects, and cross-functional stakeholders to define and evolve platform products that support scalable, reliable, and efficient payment experiences. This position is ideal for someone at the beginning of their Product Management career who is passionate about technology, enjoys solving complex problems, and wants to build products behind the scenes that enable other teams to succeed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;What you will do:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and prioritize product initiatives for platform capabilities focused on backend services and APIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Engineering and Solution Architects to design scalable platform solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business and technical requirements into clear product priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with multiple stakeholders across engineering and business teams to align objectives and product roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor product performance through metrics and data, identifying opportunities for continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em class=&quot;Highlight ht0470eb88-3706-4dc5-ab2c-3f6c07d7d49f&quot;&gt;Act&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;as the main point of contact for your product, ensuring effective communication with internal stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the delivery of platform products that enable payment integrations across different systems and applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
